  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Urdu compound word \u201cghairat-e-ashiq\u201d?",
  "response": "The Urdu compound word \"ghairat-e-ashiq\" can be broken down into two parts: \"ghairat\" and \"ashiq.\" \n\n- \"Ghairat\" generally means honor, pride, or integrity, often in the context of personal dignity and respect.\n- \"Ashiq\" means lover or someone who is deeply in love.\n\nTherefore, \"ghairat-e-ashiq\" can be understood as \"the honor or pride of a lover.\" This term often conveys the deep emotions and sentiments associated with love, including the sense of dignity and respect that a lover feels in their romantic relationship. It may also imply the protective nature of love, where a lover feels a strong sense of responsibility and honor towards their beloved.",
